  "history": {
    "en": "Developed in the early-to-mid 1800s by Australian cattlemen crossing British herding dogs (such as the Smithfield) with native Australian dingo-type dogs. Bred specifically for working ability and natural bob-tail, developing parallel to the Australian Cattle Dog as an independent herding breed.",
    "zh": "19世纪初至中期由澳大利亚牧场主培育而成，通过英国牧羊犬（如史密斯菲尔德犬）与本地澳洲野狗型犬杂交。专门为工作能力和自然短尾而繁育，与澳大利亚牧牛犬平行发展，成为一种独立的牧牛犬种。"
  },
